transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I need to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay, I can help you.

Speaker 2: I'll give you one second to pull up your profile.

Speaker 1: Okay, Jose, can you just confirm a date of birth?

Speaker 2: October 18, 1921.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: I see your VIP status.

Speaker 1: Customer, give me one second.

Speaker 2: I'm going to cancel out this refill.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect, Jose.

Speaker 2: I was able to cancel out that refill,

Speaker 1: so you'll be seeing $63.95 back on your credit card

Speaker 2: in about five business days or less.

Speaker 1: And then how's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 2: It worked well, thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, so with your VIP status,

Speaker 2: you don't have to have your refills on a monthly basis.

Speaker 1: You know, you can pause that for three to six months.

Speaker 2: A lot of people just like to go ahead and pause it.

Speaker 1: That way it keeps their prescription active

Speaker 2: and just allows you to call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 1: I could pause that for you until July 31st.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that'll be good.

Speaker 1: All right, perfect.

Speaker 2: All right, Jose, you're all set.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: No problem, have a good day.

Speaker 1: You too, bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
